<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 29 at 2:30PM MDT  by NWS Missoula</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Granite
County through 300 PM MDT...
At 230 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Drummond, moving north at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This includes Interstate 90 near mile marker 157.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
